---
import BaseLayout from '../../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Breadcrumb from '../../../components/Breadcrumb.astro';
const SITE = 'https://masterful-app.com';
const graph = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@graph': [
    {
      '@type': 'Service',
      name: 'SXO & Core SEO',
      alternateName: 'SXO',
      description:
        'SXO & Core SEO is one integrated package. Core SEO builds the technical and content foundation Google needs to rank a page: clean crawlability, topical authority through interconnected content clusters, and editorial pages that target what buyers search. SXO is the conversion layer: matching pages to search intent, tuning Core Web Vitals, structuring content for engagement, and building the internal-link journeys that move a visitor from click to action.',
      provider: { '@type': 'ProfessionalService', '@id': `${SITE}/#organization`, name: 'Masterful', url: SITE },
      serviceType: 'SXO & Core SEO',
      url: `${SITE}/services/seo/`,
      areaServed: ['United States', 'United Kingdom', 'Kenya'],
    },
    {
      '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
      itemListElement: [
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Services', item: `${SITE}/services/` },
        { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'SXO & Core SEO', item: `${SITE}/services/seo/` },
      ],
    },
  ],
};
---
<BaseLayout
  title="SXO & Core SEO | Masterful"
  description="Core SEO builds the ranking foundation and SXO turns rankings into conversions: technical SEO, topical authority and landing-page UX in one package."
  path="/services/seo/"
  navActive="services"
>
  <script type="application/ld+json" slot="schema" set:html={JSON.stringify(graph)} />
  <Breadcrumb items={[{ name: 'Home', href: '/' }, { name: 'Services', href: '/services/' }, { name: 'SXO & Core SEO' }]} />

  <main>
  <section class="service-hero wrap">
    <div class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:20px">Service No. I · SXO & Core SEO</div>
    <div class="sh-meta">
      <span class="sh-meta-item">Minimum 3 months</span>
      <span class="sh-meta-item">Flat retainer</span>
    </div>
    <h1 class="sh-headline">SXO & Core SEO:<br>found first. <em>chosen next.</em></h1>
    <p class="lead-body" style="max-width:640px;margin-bottom:24px">
      SXO & Core SEO is one package. Core SEO builds the technical and content foundation Google needs to rank a page: clean crawlability, topical authority through interconnected content clusters, and editorial pages that target what buyers search. SXO is the layer that converts the visit: matching the landing experience to search intent, tuning page speed and Core Web Vitals, structuring content for engagement, and building the internal-link journeys that move a visitor from click to action.
    </p>
    <p class="sh-tagline">Core SEO gets you found. SXO gets you chosen.</p>
    <p class="lead-body" style="max-width:640px;margin-bottom:32px;font-size:15px;color:var(--mute)">
      Google now factors page experience and engagement signals into how it ranks pages. A click that leads to an immediate bounce tells Google the page failed the query. SXO addresses that: it makes pages fast, readable, and structured so visitors stay and act.
    </p>
    <p class="lead-body" style="max-width:640px;margin-bottom:32px;font-size:15px;color:var(--mute)">
      The <a href="/work/dreyvision-marketing/" class="link-ul" style="color:var(--orange)">Drey Vision Marketing case study</a> shows this in numbers: organic visits up 50%, click-through up 45%, and average position up 80 places.
    </p>
    <a href="/audit/" class="btn btn-orange">Run a free audit</a>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars wrap">
    <div class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:32px">Core SEO: What We Build <span class="kicker-num">/ XII</span></div>
    <div class="pillar-grid">
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Technical foundations</h3>
        <p>Crawlability, Core Web Vitals, schema markup, indexation, llms.txt. The architecture Google needs to understand and rank your site.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Topical authority</h3>
        <p>A cluster of interconnected content that tells Google your brand owns a subject. One article does not build authority. A 14-page anchor set does.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Editorial content</h3>
        <p>Pages written to rank for specific queries at the right stage of the buyer journey. Briefed, written, and published by Masterful.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Monthly reporting</h3>
        <p>Rankings, impressions, and position shifts tracked against your baseline. Every change explained. No dashboard login required.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="pillars wrap" style="border-top:1px solid var(--rule)">
    <div class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:32px">SXO: The Conversion Layer <span class="kicker-num">/ XII</span></div>
    <div class="pillar-grid">
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Search-intent matching</h3>
        <p>We map what searchers expect when they click, then build the page around that expectation. A visitor from "best CRM for law firms" needs a comparison, not a homepage. Wrong match, wasted click.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Landing-page UX and conversion path</h3>
        <p>We audit and restructure the path from landing to action: layout, hierarchy, friction points, and the CTA sequence that moves a visitor forward without confusion.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Core Web Vitals and page experience</h3>
        <p>LCP, INP, and CLS measured on real templates and brought inside Google's thresholds. Visitors leave slow pages before reading them. Google notices when they do.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Content structure for engagement</h3>
        <p>Headings, paragraph length, reading level, and information hierarchy structured so visitors read further. Dwell time is a ranking signal, and poor structure is the most common cause of low dwell.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Internal-link journeys</h3>
        <p>We plan the next-page sequence from every landing page: the right links, in the right positions, to the right destinations. A visitor who follows an internal link is more likely to convert and less likely to bounce back to Google.</p>
      </div>
      <div class="pillar">
        <h3>Engagement-signal monitoring</h3>
        <p>Bounce rate, dwell time, scroll depth, and pogo-sticking tracked monthly. When a signal degrades, we diagnose the page before Google penalises it.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Sub-pages -->
  <section class="wrap" style="padding:48px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)">
    <div class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:32px">Inside SXO & Core SEO <span class="kicker-num">/ XII</span></div>
    <div class="pillar-grid">
      <a href="/services/seo/technical-seo/" class="pillar" style="display:block;text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <h3>Technical SEO →</h3>
        <p>Crawlability, indexing, Core Web Vitals, and site health fixed so Google and AI crawlers can read your site.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/seo/seo-audit/" class="pillar" style="display:block;text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <h3>SEO audit →</h3>
        <p>A full technical and content audit with a prioritised 90-day fix list, not a 200-page PDF nobody reads.</p>
      </a>
      <a href="/services/seo/local-seo-nairobi/" class="pillar" style="display:block;text-decoration:none;color:inherit">
        <h3>Local SEO Nairobi →</h3>
        <p>Google Business Profile, local citations, and reviews that rank you in the Nairobi map pack.</p>
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap" style="padding:48px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule)">
    <div class="kicker" style="margin-bottom:32px">What This Is Not</div>
    <ul style="list-style:none;display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0">
      <li style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,26px);line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-0.01em;padding:20px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);color:var(--mute)">Link farms.</li>
      <li style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,26px);line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-0.01em;padding:20px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);color:var(--mute)">AI-generated bulk content.</li>
      <li style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,26px);line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-0.01em;padding:20px 0;border-bottom:1px solid var(--rule);color:var(--mute)">Keyword stuffing.</li>
      <li style="font-family:var(--serif);font-size:clamp(18px,2.2vw,26px);line-height:1.2;letter-spacing:-0.01em;padding:20px 0;color:var(--mute)">Monthly reports with no action item attached.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section class="wrap section-sm" style="display:flex;justify-content:space-between;align-items:center;border-top:1px solid var(--rule)">
    <a href="/services/" class="t-mono link-ul" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mute)">← All services</a>
    <div class="silo-links">
      <a href="/services/aeo/" class="t-mono link-ul" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--orange)">AEO →</a>
      <a href="/services/geo/" class="t-mono link-ul" style="font-size:11px;letter-spacing:0.06em;text-transform:uppercase;color:var(--mute)">GEO →</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="on-dark" style="padding:80px 32px;text-align:center">
    <div class="wrap" style="max-width:600px">
      <p style="font-size:15px;line-height:1.65;color:rgba(244,240,232,0.65);max-width:440px;margin:0 auto 24px">The audit tells you where the technical gaps are before we quote anything.</p>
      <a href="/audit/" class="btn btn-orange">Run a free audit</a>
    </div>
  </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>
